<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="56" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Minister <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-17"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(The minister is informed, relative to immigration to South Carolina,
                            that the advance of passage money to an alien does not violate the
                            contract-labor law, but that an alien must prove affirmatively that he
                            will not become a public charge and submit to examination as to other
                            legal requirements.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>